raw_logic_programs:
Predicates:
InfectiousDisease(x) ::: x is an infectious disease.
CausedBy(x, y) ::: x is caused by y.
OccurIn(x, y) ::: x can occur in y.
Human(x) ::: x is a human.
Mammal(x) ::: x is a mammal.
Animal(x) ::: x is an animal.
SymptonOf(x, y) ::: x is a sympton of y.
FeelTiredWhenGet(x, y) ::: x feels tired when they get y.
Premises:
InfectiousDisease(monkeypox) ∧ CausedBy(monkeypox, monkeypoxVirus) ::: Monkeypox is an infectious disease caused by the monkeypox virus.
∀x (Animal(x) → OccurIn(monkeypoxVirus, x)) ::: Monkeypox virus can occur in certain animals, including humans.
∀x (Human(x) → Mammal(x)) ::: Humans are mammals.
∀x (Mammal(x) → Animal(x)) ::: Mammals are animals.
SymptonOf(fever, monkeypox) ∧ SymptonOf(headache, monkeypox) ∧ SymptonOf(musclePains, monkeypox) ∧ SymptonOf(feelingTired, monkeypox) ::: Symptons of Monkeypox include fever, headache, muscle pains, feeling tired, and so on.
∀x (Human(x) → FeelTiredWhenGet(x, glu)) ::: People feel tired when they get a glu.
Conclusion:
SymptonOf(coughing, monkeypox) ::: Symptons of Monkeypox include coughing.

Conclusion:
SymptonOf(coughing, monkeypox) ::: Symptons of Monkeypox include coughing.

thoughts.question: Question: Based on the above information, is the following statement true, false, or uncertain? Symptons of Monkeypox include coughing.
thoughts.options: Options: A) True, B) False, C) Uncertain
raw_logic_programs:
Predicates:
InfectiousDisease(x) ::: x is an infectious disease.
CausedBy(x, y) ::: x is caused by y.
OccurIn(x, y) ::: x can occur in y.
Human(x) ::: x is a human.
Mammal(x) ::: x is a mammal.
Animal(x) ::: x is an animal.
SymptonOf(x, y) ::: x is a sympton of y.
FeelTiredWhenGet(x, y) ::: x feels tired when they get y.
Premises:
InfectiousDisease(monkeypox) ∧ CausedBy(monkeypox, monkeypoxVirus) ::: Monkeypox is an infectious disease caused by the monkeypox virus.
∀x (Animal(x) → OccurIn(monkeypoxVirus, x)) ::: Monkeypox virus can occur in certain animals, including humans.
∀x (Human(x) → Mammal(x)) ::: Humans are mammals.
∀x (Mammal(x) → Animal(x)) ::: Mammals are animals.
SymptonOf(fever, monkeypox) ∧ SymptonOf(headache, monkeypox) ∧ SymptonOf(musclePains, monkeypox) ∧ SymptonOf(feelingTired, monkeypox) ::: Symptons of Monkeypox include fever, headache, muscle pains, feeling tired, and so on.
∀x (Human(x) → FeelTiredWhenGet(x, glu)) ::: People feel tired when they get a glu.
Conclusion:
SymptonOf(coughing, monkeypox) ::: Symptons of Monkeypox include coughing.

thoughts.question: Question: Based on the above information, is the following statement true, false, or uncertain? Symptons of Monkeypox include coughing.
thoughts.options: Options: A) True, B) False, C) Uncertain
raw_logic_programs:
Predicates:
InfectiousDisease(x) ::: x is an infectious disease.
CausedBy(x, y) ::: x is caused by y.
OccurIn(x, y) ::: x can occur in y.
Human(x) ::: x is a human.
Mammal(x) ::: x is a mammal.
Animal(x) ::: x is an animal.
SymptonOf(x, y) ::: x is a sympton of y.
FeelTiredWhenGet(x, y) ::: x feels tired when they get y.
Premises:
InfectiousDisease(monkeypox) ∧ CausedBy(monkeypox, monkeypoxVirus) ::: Monkeypox is an infectious disease caused by the monkeypox virus.
∀x (Animal(x) → OccurIn(monkeypoxVirus, x)) ::: Monkeypox virus can occur in certain animals, including humans.
∀x (Human(x) → Mammal(x)) ::: Humans are mammals.
∀x (Mammal(x) → Animal(x)) ::: Mammals are animals.
SymptonOf(fever, monkeypox) ∧ SymptonOf(headache, monkeypox) ∧ SymptonOf(musclePains, monkeypox) ∧ SymptonOf(feelingTired, monkeypox) ::: Symptons of Monkeypox include fever, headache, muscle pains, feeling tired, and so on.
∀x (Human(x) → FeelTiredWhenGet(x, glu)) ::: People feel tired when they get a glu.
Conclusion:
SymptonOf(coughing, monkeypox) ::: Symptons of Monkeypox include coughing.
